  "interpretation": "Illustrative n=10 hierarchical run across all tiers (total intelligence plus the three IST subscales). Demographics-led tiers rank-recover the total strongly (T1 rho=0.82) and the brain-only tiers moderately (B3 rho=0.32, B1 0.21) while the coarse connectome alone is ~0 (B2), matching the 100-subject batch pattern. The subscales are recovered with usable signal at the full tier (memory rho=0.52, crystallised 0.45). CAVEAT: the 10 subjects were chosen to span the full IST range (87 to 280), which inflates rank correlations relative to a representative sample, so these values are optimistic and NOT comparable to the representative 100-subject batch. This demonstrates the hierarchical output and the pipeline, not a benchmark."
